This paper deals with description logics (DLs), which are a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI) and logic (LO). The paper specifically focuses on the satisfiability and query answering problems in DLs with global and local cardinality constraints, which are commonly used in databases (DB) and natural language processing (CL). Finally, the paper introduces a new DL, ALCSCC++, which is a variant of the well-known ALC DL, further supporting the likelihood of cs.DL as a possible sub-category.
